10 OFFENSES THAT ARE INELIGIBLE FOR MERITORIOUS
11 FURLOUGH; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
12
13
Subtitle
14
15 TO ADD SECOND DEGREE MURDER TO THE LIST
16 OF OFFENSES THAT ARE INELIGIBLE FOR
17 MERITORIOUS FURLOUGH.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
20
21 12-29-102. Inmates denied participation in furlough programs.
22 A person who is convicted of any of the following offenses shall be
23 ineligible to participate in any meritorious furlough program conducted by or
24 for the Division of Correction:
25 (1) Capital murder, § 5-10-101;
26 (2) Murder in the first degree, § 5-10-102;
27 (3) Murder in the second degree, § 5-10-103;
28 (4) Kidnapping, § 5-11-102;
29 (4)(5) Rape, § 5-14-103;
30 (5)(6) Any other offense concerning sexual offenses under § 5-
31 14-101 et seq.;
32 (6)(7) An offense concerning sexual exploitation of children
33 under the Arkansas Protection of Children Against Exploitation Act of 1979, §
34 5-27-301 et seq.;
35 (7)(8) An offense concerning use of children in sexual
36 performances under § 5-27-401 et seq.; or
